high level goals
taking notes in vim mode (two hand, shift and special opposite)
coding and flipping to a browser
researching in a browser (one hand, command, control, shift, tab adjacent)
coding in an ide
games like minecraft, league (one hand, letters adjacent)
esoteric shortcuts

analysis
special is shi, com, con, opt for 16 combinations

factors
type -> little finger shift opposite
type -> either thumb space, enter, backspace
type -> benign little finger adjacent
no need for shift adjacent
no need for command or control with special
little finger special adjacent
vim -> left thumb escape
browse -> left command or control or shift with tab
browse -> left command with shift and letter
tty -> left control with letter
calc -> shift and control with enter
no need for shift with backspace
ergo -> no adjacent modifiers with little finger
type -> need to consider the delete key
mac -> option is sometimes useful e.g. command option v
command could make shift behave backwards?

implications
left thumb has command, control, space
right thumb has backspace, escape
either thumb has space, enter, backspace, escape, ?, ?
left little finger has shift, tab, ?
right little finger has shift, quote, ?

aliases
⌘ is command
o is option
c is control
↑ is shift
r is return
e is escape
← is backspace
_ is space
→ is tab

